snippet.textDisplay:
I just watched the fight for the first time. First I watched it in a bullshit zoomed version and now I watched the real thing. It was cut up in parts but still it was clear. And it’s what I suspected lol I agree with most people. For sure first 2 rounds was Reyes. Round 3 maybe Reyes maybe draw I don’t know. Rounds 4 and 5 definitely Jones ESPECIALLY round 5 he dominated him in the most important round. Let me make a few points of what’s going on becuz I think y’all are biased and delusional. All Reyes fans please read all these points cuz I think it’s very important-

1- I did this same thing with the Santos fight. I wanted Jones to lose so bad that just cuz Santos was doing well and hurting him I over imagined that he’s beating him but he really wasn’t. Y’all hate Jones so much and u want him to lose y’all are just very biased view of what Reyes did. Yea Reyes killed him in rounds 1 and 2. But then Jones destroyed him in 4 and 5. Which rounds are more important???? Championship rounds are far more important then the early rounds. And if they kept fighting for round 6 and 7 y’all can’t tell me Reyes would win lol. He was gassed out and just trying to make it to the end. Jones was much more fresh and if they kept fighting it woulda been the same as round 5. I think that’s tell telling of what’s goin on in the fight. It matters who would win if they keep fighting

2- Jones is one of the greatest fighters ever. We talkin about taking the belt from him on a decision. Do y’all really think Reyes did enough to do that???? He fought great for the first half of the fight he beat up jones the whole first half. But then the 2nd half he sat around and got whooped especially round 5 the most important round he got destroyed. Championship rounds far more valuable then 1 and 2 Give me a break. There’s no way in hell you can back pettle the entire 2nd half of the fight and get beat on then think you gonna win a close decision vs Jon Jones. Are y’all fukin kidding me??? Round 4 and 5 he did nothing but back pettle and get beat up. If anyone thinks he’s gonna win a decision and take away the belt on that is fukin crazy. You not taking a belt from one of the goats like that lol y’all have to know better then this cmon. You can’t get destroyed in the championship rounds and expect a decision win. Reyes is delusional and so is all of his fans

3- if Reyes truly believed he won the fight. I didn’t hear him ask for a rematch one time during all his crying in the post fight interview lol the reporters had to pull it outta him. For a person truly believed he won the fight and he’s better then Jones. The first thing he shoulda said in the interview is demand his rematch. I didn’t hear that one time from him. Only complaining how he won and robbed. He said everything in the fukin world except demanding his rematch lol I mean y’all tell me what this is. A great speaker literally said everything except asking for his rematch. I mean cmon. Fukin Jones the dude who won the fight was talkin about a rematch more then him lol

4- the truth is he didn’t do enough to win a decision. Did he fight great? Hell yea he did he out fought Jones badly in the first 2 rounds. Round 3 maybe him or a draw. But then the most crucial rounds championship rounds he got destroyed. Round 5 got totally destroyed. Not enough to win a decision period. He fought amazing for the first half but that’s not enough to change belts on a decision. Then after the fight he’s here talking like he’s the 2nd best ever coming lol it ain’t so he’s delusional. He fought great against Jones on this one night. But that’s one matchup on one night. Could be a favorable matchup. Styles make fights y’all know this. Let him beat Anthony Smith. Let him beat Thiago Santos. Beat all the people Jones beat then you can talk like you the 2nd coming. There’s levels cmon. He beat a bunch of nobody’s up till now. Jones been beating a bunch of champions his whole career. Beat all the other top guys in the 205 division then talk. Personally I think 2016 DC would knock him out. Anthony Johnson and Gus and others like that. All I’m sayin is he’s gotta do more then fight great on one night. He fought great vs Jones on one night and talks like he’s the 2nd goat ever. Doesn’t work that way. Beat other light heavy contenders then talk

5- this is just one example. When DC was in the 205 division a few years ago. I think that DC would destroy Reyes. He would either walk him down or out wrestle him. Reyes had a favorable matchup vs Jones. Styles make fights everyone knows this. In any sport especially MMA. He talks like he’s the 2nd best in the world and he’s not. He had a very favorable matchup against a weakened Jones. I think this is the weakest Jones has ever been in his career. Jones couldn’t hold him down he almost did but he couldn’t cuz the physical strength wasn’t there. DC would hold him down...............
He didn’t even wanna engage vs Jon Jones lol he was hitting and running. Imagine if DC engages with him

Now let me here opinions

snippet.textDisplay:
ROUND 1: 10-9 Reyes
Personally, I think it was a slip. But 10-8 if you counted the slip as a knock down.
ROUND 2: 10-9 Reyes
Most Ive seen Jones struggle with anyone.
ROUND 3: 10-10
Reyes began to lose the pace control here.
ROUND 4: 10-9 Jones
It became clear that Jones' strategy was to edge him out late with conditioning.
Round 5: 10-9 Jones
I wouldnt argue if a judge had this one 10-8. Reyes was gassed and his output dipped quite noticeably.
Overall, Reyes was more active and inflicted more damage than I think Jones was prepared for. Also, his takedown defense was amazing. He just seemed a lot stronger than Jones the way he was stuffing the wrestling and powering back up to his feet. Jones was had better conditioning. He didnt give up on scoring takedowns, and yes, even non-fruitful take downs matter. Jones had a better overall strategy for the long fight. Reyes did damage, but Jones never really seemed like he was in fight-jeopardizing danger. He was never noticably wincing, limping, or protecting a particular body part. The early damage never caused Jones to abandon his gameplan or refrain from trying to engage or control the pace. Jones' gameplan ,on the other hand, was clearly effective. You saw that clearly in rounds 4-5 when Reyes gassed, allowing the champ to score vital garbage time points that edged him back on the cards. But at best, I think it was a draw.
